<TITLE> Punishment to 4 VIP detainees relaxed </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 27 (bdnews24.com)Jail authorities Thursday decided to relax the punishment to four VIP detainees, accused of breaching the jail code by using cell phones, a senior prisons official said. The duration of suspension of their division was reduced to one week from three months, deputy inspector general of prisons Major Shamsul Haider Siddiqui said. The decision will come into effect from Thursday, he said. The four detainees are barrister Nazmul Huda, Altaf Hossain Chowdhury, Salahuddin Quader Chowdhury and Mohiuddin Khan Alamgir. The authorities on March 25 suspended their division for three months for breaching jail code. Another detainee, Sigma Huda, who is also accused of breaching the jail code, was stripped of the right to meet with relatives. Nazmul Huda and Altaf Hossain Chowdhury are now in Narayanganj jail, Salauddin Quader Chowdhury in Bogra and Mohiuddin Khan Alamgir in Kashimpur jail. Sigma Huda is in Dhaka Central Jail. The DIG said some other detainees had faced the same allegations. Six of them were shifted to jails outside Dhaka. bdnews24.
